Package jsx.ui.event

Event objects and their handlers for the general user interfaces.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
OnChange Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Change type.
OnCheck Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Check type.
OnClick Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Click type.
OnClose Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Close type.
OnDblClick Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the DblClick type.
OnMouseDown Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the MouseDown type.
OnMouseMove Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the MouseMove type.
OnMouseOut Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the MouseOut type.
OnMouseOver Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the MouseOver type.
OnMouseUp Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the MouseUp type.
OnPopup Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Popup type.
OnProgress Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Progress type.
OnRender Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Render type.
OnResize Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Resize type.
OnStyle Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Style type.
OnUncheck Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the Check type.
 

Class Summary
Change A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse click event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
Check A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse click event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
Click A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse click event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
Close A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the element wrapped by the widget pops up on the display stack.
DblClick A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse double-click event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
MouseDown A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse down event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
MouseMove A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse move event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
MouseOut A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse out event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
MouseOver A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse over event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
MouseUp A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse up event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
Popup A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the element wrapped by the widget pops up on the display stack.
Position<T> An abstract type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the mouse has position data to report to the element wrapped by the widget.
Progress A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the style of the element wrapped by the widget has just been changed.
Render A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the component or the component wrapped by the widget has just been rendered.
Resize A type of high level events that may be fired from a view port container when the size of its window has just been changed.
Style A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the style of the element wrapped by the widget has just been changed.
Uncheck A type of high level events that may be fired from a source widget when the browser mouse click event occurs on the element wrapped by the widget.
 

Package jsx.ui.event Description
